Community Guidelines
Dear users:
Lemo is committed to providing services including real-time voice, video call, text & picture editing and updates posting, but users are also bound by the rules listed below. If there is any illegal content posted or disseminated on this platform, please let us know.
Lemo takes tough line against obscenity, vulgarity, violence, disruptive behaviors and instigation of crimes. Let’s work together for an upright and healthy Lemo!
Rules and Disciplinary Action for Chat Room Owners
Chat room owners are duty-bound to regulate their rooms and respond to violations but, if not, they will be subjected to punishment along with the involved violators. Owners in any of the following scenarios shall receive an ID ban:
1. Failing to cope with illicit content against the User Behavior Code
2. Over 15 in one room involving in insult, slander, troublemaking and other practices disruptive of chat room order.
(PS: Owners shall not be subject to joint punishment as long as they [report] or [boot out] the malicious troublemakers the moment they spot them.)
User Behavior Code and Disciplinary Action
Users shall keep to the User Behavior Code when using Lemo. Any user in the following cases will be silenced or receive or receive a ban on account.
1. Erotic acts
• Dissemination of sexually explicit content, including yet not confined to eroticism, whoring, hook-up, sexually arousing breaths, one-night stand, dirty talks & texts and third-party accounts & links.
• Sexually accosted behaviors with innuendos, including yet not confined to appearing in underwear, close-ups of body parts such as chest, hip and legs, and perverted fan services.
2. Vulgar acts
Acts instigating vulgar behaviors including yet not confined to mic kissing, sexual panting and scream, showing underwear, sexual moves and male users appearing topless.
3. Illicit acts including yet not confined to:
• Reactionary acts
Breach to the general principles enshrined in the Constitution of the People’s Republic of China, damage to national security, subverting the State power, incitation of ethnic hatred, propagation of cult beliefs and feudal superstition, and unlawful assembly.
• Drug trafficking and the sale and purchase of counterfeit banknotes, guns, ammunition as well as regulated knives, illicit drugs and fake certificates.
• Posting content involved with gamble gathering, gambling strategies and things along that line.
• Employing and/or instigate others to engage in terrorist violence.
4.Immoral acts
Provoking, threatening, slandering, and insulting others, causing damages to others’ interests, illegal gathering, holding funerals with malicious intents and other acts that destabilize Lemo.
5.Advertising acts
Cheerleading for or recommend others, in order to seek profits, to buy and/or use products that do not belong to Lemo by posting any ad-related information on the platform. Specifically, these acts shall include advertising other apps, products
                and shops, publishing accounts of third-party platforms (Facebook, Google and/or phone numbers) to redirect users and other behaviors that involve fraud, blatant wooing for sexually tantalizing wheezes, and dirty talks, and that involve
                fundraising advertisements.
6. Posting bloody, violent, horrible, disgusting and other unpleasant contents, including yet not confined to:
• Real pictures where human and/or animals are killed, crippled, shot, pierced and/or tortured.
• Paintings or texts that depict violence, self-mutilation and/or child abuse.
• Bloody and horrible scenarios
7. Using plug-in software or third-party tools to modify coins, gifts and registration, and other acts disturbing Lemo’s operation.
8. Abnormal uses of account
Users in any of the following conditions shall receive a control or ban on their accounts:
• Hoarding multiple Lemo accounts, accumulating golden coins with multiple accounts and acts disruptive of Lemo’s operation.
• Abnormal attempts of account login and top-up, and other signifiers of risks in accounts.
